Class DmcObjectName

java.lang.Object
  org.dmd.dmc.DmcObjectName
All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
CamelCaseName, DmcHierarchicObjectName, DmtStringName, IntegerName, LongName, StringName, UUIDName
public abstract class DmcObjectName
extends java.lang.Object
implements DmcMappedAttributeIF, java.lang.Comparable<DmcObjectName>, java.io.Serializable

The DmcObjectName class provides a base type from which all types that represent object names should be derived. The common base allows for wrapping of these types by generated code that makes object naming easier to handle in a consistent way.

getNameString

public abstract java.lang.String getNameString()

getPresentationString

public abstract java.lang.String getPresentationString()
Internally, names may not be particularly suited to display in user interfaces. This method should be overloaded to provide an informative presentation name.

Returns:
A string.

setNameString

public abstract void setNameString(java.lang.String n)
                            throws DmcValueException
Implementing classes must overload this method to initialize their name properly with the String form of their name. This can basically be seen as implying that you must have a constructor for your name implementation that takes a String as argument. We need setNameString() so that we can create DmcTypeNamedObjectREF values based on a String.

Parameters:
n - The name value as a String.
Throws:
DmcValueException
